To cite "clustDDist" in publications use:

  Kejzar, N., Korenjak-Cerne, S. & Batagelj, V. (2009). Clustering discrete distributions: The case of patent citations (Submitted)

A BibTeX entry for LaTeX users is

  @unpublished{,
    title = {Clustering discrete distributions: The case of patent citations},
    author = {Kejzar, N., Korenjak-Cerne, S. & Batagelj, V.},
    organization = {R Foundation for Statistical Computing},
    year = {2009},
    note = {paper submitted}	
  }

We have invested a lot of time and effort in creating R, please cite it when
using it for data analysis. See also ‘citation("pkgname")’ for citing R
packages.
